WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.320 --> 00:00:13.000
Scholars in the Social Sciences and Humanities 

2
00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:19.000
make use of monographs to communicate research data, debate ideas, and shift paradigms.

3
00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:20.440
Rooted in the print format, 

4
00:00:20.440 --> 00:00:23.480
the monograph is now evolving toward Open Access, 

5
00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:26.120
becoming an enriched digital document 

6
00:00:26.120 --> 00:00:28.640
which can be discovered, cited, linked 

7
00:00:28.640 --> 00:00:32.440
and annotated in a multi-modal environment.

8
00:00:32.440 --> 00:00:34.880
But the transition to Open Access 

9
00:00:34.880 --> 00:00:36.200
comes with conceptual, 

10
00:00:36.200 --> 00:00:37.560
economical 

11
00:00:37.560 --> 00:00:38.960
and technical barriers, 

12
00:00:38.960 --> 00:00:41.520
from reading habits and quality assurance, 

13
00:00:41.520 --> 00:00:44.160
to licensing and data storage demands.

14
00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:48.080
To overcome these obstacles,

15
00:00:48.080 --> 00:00:51.280
the European Union funded the HIRMEOS project. 

16
00:00:51.280 --> 00:00:54.280
HIRMEOS integrates five existing digital platforms

17
00:00:54.280 --> 00:00:56.720
on which more than 10.000 open access,

18
00:00:56.720 --> 00:00:58.840
peer reviewed monographs are published, 

19
00:00:58.840 --> 00:01:01.000
in more than 10 languages.

20
00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:06.840
HIRMEOS adds new services to ensure better discoverability and quality certification of books,

21
00:01:06.840 --> 00:01:09.440
and provides tools for named entity recognition,

22
00:01:09.440 --> 00:01:13.000
annotation and metrics to enhance their usage.

23
00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:16.480
These implementations prepare the way for OPERAS:

24
00:01:16.480 --> 00:01:19.360
a wider research infrastructure aimed at developing

25
00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:22.120
more inclusive open scholarly communication

26
00:01:22.120 --> 00:01:25.560
and exploring emerging publishing models.

27
00:01:29.160 --> 00:01:32.040
First, HIRMEOS sets up a common framework,

28
00:01:32.040 --> 00:01:36.400
integrating standard identifiers and a shared certification service.

29
00:01:36.400 --> 00:01:41.280
Three new data sources identify authors, documents and funding institutions. 

30
00:01:41.280 --> 00:01:42.520
For researchers,

31
00:01:42.520 --> 00:01:45.880
this means it is easier to cite books and verify sources,

32
00:01:45.880 --> 00:01:49.440
as well as to cross link documents and find scholarly contributions.

33
00:01:49.440 --> 00:01:52.800
By adopting a system of peer review certification,

34
00:01:52.800 --> 00:01:55.800
HIRMEOS aims at giving scholars and libraries confidence

35
00:01:55.800 --> 00:01:59.840
in the quality of the monographs they acquire and read.

36
00:02:00.080 --> 00:02:05.000
Three advanced services allow for new forms of interaction with the documents.

37
00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:08.240
The first tool recognizes named entities types

38
00:02:08.240 --> 00:02:09.000
person name,

39
00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:09.760
location,

40
00:02:09.760 --> 00:02:11.280
organization in the text 

41
00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:13.120
and identifies them correctly;

42
00:02:13.120 --> 00:02:17.320
the second tool enables readers to directly add annotations to monographs,

43
00:02:17.320 --> 00:02:20.240
pioneering new forms of commentary and peer review,

44
00:02:20.240 --> 00:02:25.200
and transforming the monograph into a place of open discussion between authors and readers.

45
00:02:25.200 --> 00:02:26.040
Thirdly,

46
00:02:26.040 --> 00:02:30.320
Usage Metrics and Altmetrics describe the reach and impact of a monograph,

47
00:02:30.320 --> 00:02:31.800
measuring downloads,

48
00:02:31.800 --> 00:02:35.960
views and citations in scholarly literature and social media. 

49
00:02:37.120 --> 00:02:39.720
We intend the Open Access Digital Monograph 

50
00:02:39.720 --> 00:02:43.120
as a medium that completes and enhances the printed document, 

51
00:02:43.120 --> 00:02:50.280
uncovering new methodologies and research fields in the Social Sciences and Humanities. 

52
00:02:51.440 --> 00:02:57.600
Follow Hirmeos and Operas’ roadmap at hirmeos.eu and operas-eu.org 

53
00:02:57.600 --> 00:03:00.760
and join the discussion to develop better ways of acquiring

54
00:03:00.760 --> 00:03:03.840
and disseminating open knowledge.

